# codex-coverage-floor.baseline — ratified per-file statement-coverage floors
# for the structured Codex input-driver reactor files (agent-input-substrate
# M2, T9; harness-acceptance-design §"Coverage floor").
#
# Measured 2026-07-15 on base phase1-session-restart-substrate 5c68bc31 via:
#   go test -count=1 -coverprofile=<tmp> ./internal/codexinput/... ./internal/codexdriver/...
# (in-package coverage only — the driver packages' own tests + the T9 harness's
# in-package driver exercise; cross-package coverpkg excluded, matching the
# keeper §6.4 command).
#
# The RATIFIED floors below sit a hair under the measured values — a RATCHET:
# coverage may not drop below these. Raising a floor after an improvement is a
# normal follow-up; lowering one requires the same scrutiny as editing any
# protected rule file.
#
# Format: <file-path-under-internal/> <floor-pct>
codexinput/reactor.go 70.0
codexdriver/driver.go 73.0
codexdriver/session.go 86.0
